parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Power steering failure can cause the vehicle to become difficult to steer, leading to loss of control, accidents, or injuries. In extreme cases, it can also cause the steering system to lock, making it impossible to steer the vehicle.
symptoms: Excessive effort needed to turn the steering wheel
steering becomes difficult to turn in cold weather.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Steering rack failure can cause the vehicle to lose steering control, leading to accidents or injuries. It can also cause the steering system to leak fluid, leading to further damage to the system.
A-frame failure can cause the steering system to become loose, leading to loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: mount where the A-frame bolts in cracks

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failure can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of control, and in some cases, result in a fire, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
Ignition system failure can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of control, and may also cause difficulty starting the vehicle.
The failure of the seat belt can lead to ejection from the vehicle, resulting in serious injuries or fatalities, even in low-speed collisions.
symptoms: The seat belt disengages during a collision
the seat belt webbing tears or splits
the shoulder belt fails to restrain the driver
the seat belt does not retract properly.
